properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued March 2 at 3:08AM PST until March 3 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the first Small Craft Advisory, west winds 15 to 25
kt. For the second Small Craft Advisory, west winds 20 to 30 kt.

* WHERE...Central U. S. Waters Strait Of Juan De Fuca.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 4 AM PST early this
morning. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 1 PM this
afternoon to 10 AM PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
A Small Craft Advisory means that wind speeds of 21 to 33 knots
and/or seas 10 feet or higher are expected to produce hazardous
wave conditions to small craft. Inexperienced mariners,
especially those operating smaller vessels should avoid
navigating in these conditions.
